content: [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) is a sovereign [island country](/wiki/Island_country) in [maritime Southeast Asia](/wiki/Maritime_Southeast_Asia). A [global city](/wiki/Global_city), it has a highly developed [market economy](/wiki/Market_economy), based historically on extended [entrepôt](/wiki/Entrep%C3%B4t) trade and more recently as a [financial hub](/wiki/Financial_hub) as well. Its economy is known as the most freest, most innovative, most competitive, most dynamic and most business-friendly in the world by various multinational economists, think-tanks and organisations. Singapore is also consistently ranked as one of the least corrupt countries in the world, and the most transparent in all of Asia on the [Corruption Perceptions Index](/wiki/Corruption_Perceptions_Index) (CPI). Singapore is a wealthy country, and is one of the original [Four Asian Tigers](/wiki/Four_Asian_Tigers), having also surpassed its peers in terms of [GDP per capita](/wiki/List_of_countries_by_GDP_(PPP)_per_capita), being the second highest in the world. Between 1965 and 1995, growth rates averaged around 6 per cent per annum, transforming the living standards of the population within a single generation. To start a business in Singapore, business owners have to register with the [Accounting and Corporate Regulatory Authority](/wiki/Accounting_and_Corporate_Regulatory_Authority) (ACRA). ACRA is the national regulator and company registrar of business entities, accountants and service providers in Singapore. ## Largest firms This list shows firms in the [Fortune Global 500](/wiki/Fortune_Global_500), which ranks firms by total revenue for 2024. Only the top five firms (if available) are included as a sample.
